<subSubSection id="C3365C99FFEB7B48FF08F92B358A0EF7" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B930F12FFEB7B48FF08F92B358A0EF7" blockId="16.[168,776,1636,1926]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">
<emphasis id="B958D300FFEB7B48FF08F92B34C80FAF" inLineHeading="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B958D300FFEB7B48FF08F92B35120FCD" bold="true" box="[206,316,1700,1724]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C7491FFEB7B48FD96F92B34C80FAF" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperlopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis id="B958D300FFEB7B48FD96F92B34C80FAF" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">Hyperlopha crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
in general fascia, even though is slightly larger. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C7491FFEB7B48FF6EF967351E0F8E" box="[168,304,1767,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperlopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis id="B958D300FFEB7B48FF6EF967351E0F8E" box="[168,304,1767,1791]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">H. crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as a new species by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD72E3FFEB7B48FD10F968356E0E50" author="Holloway JD" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" pagination="1 - 529" refId="ref11463" refString="Holloway JD (2005) The moths of Borneo (parts 15 &amp; 16): family Noctuidae, subfamily Catocalinae. The Malayan Nature Journal 58: 1 - 529." type="journal article" year="2005">Holloway (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. He differentiated 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C7491FFEB7B48FDD1F885368E0E50" authorityName="Walker sensu Holloway" authorityYear="1976" box="[535,672,1801,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperlopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristifera">
<emphasis id="B958D300FFEB7B48FDD1F885368E0E50" box="[535,672,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">H. cristifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C7491FFEB7B48FD2BF88535240E32" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperlopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis id="B958D300FFEB7B48FD2BF88535240E32" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">H. crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the male genitalia. We have collected only female specimen of 
<emphasis id="B958D300FFEB7B48FE79F8C236670E15" box="[447,585,1868,1892]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">
<taxonomicName id="4C2C7491FFEB7B48FE79F8C2366B0E15" authorityName="Walker sensu Holloway" authorityYear="1976" box="[447,581,1868,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperlopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristifera">H. cristifera</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
More research is needed for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
